data.comment: The match is underway at Behrn Arena.
Norrkoping have been awarded a corner by Fredrik Klitte.
In the minute 3, At Behrn Arena, Norrkoping are penalized for being offside.
Orebro awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Deniz Hummet of Orebro gets in a strike, but is off target.
In the minute 5, Goal kick for Norrkoping at Behrn Arena.
Fredrik Klitte signals a free kick to Orebro in their own half.
Orebro awarded a free kick in their own half.
In the minute 7, Free kick for Norrkoping in their own half.
Norrkoping needs to be cautious. Orebro have an attacking throw-in.
In Orebro a free kick has been awarded the home team.
In the minute 10, Jake Larsson (Orebro) gets in a strike but the shot is blocked by a defender.
Corner awarded to Orebro.
Fredrik Klitte signals a throw-in for Norrkoping, close to Orebro's area.
In the minute 12, Norrkoping attack but Christoffer Nyman's header doesn't find the target.
Orebro have a goal kick.
In Orebro Norrkoping's Pontus Almqvist is caught offside.
In the minute 14, Fredrik Klitte signals a free kick to Orebro.
Throw-in for Orebro in their own half.
It's a goal kick for the home team in Orebro.
In the minute 17, Orebro to take a throw-in in Norrkoping territory.
Free kick for Orebro in the half of Norrkoping.
Orebro's Johan Martensson misses with an attempt on goal.
In the minute 17, Ball goes out of play for a Norrkoping goal kick.
Fredrik Klitte awards Norrkoping a goal kick.
Free kick Norrkoping.
In the minute 22, In Orebro a free kick has been awarded the home team.
In Orebro, Nahir Besara of Orebro is presented with a shooting opportunity. But the strike is blocked by the covering defence.
Corner awarded to Orebro.
In the minute 23, Norrkoping awarded a free kick in their own half.
Fredrik Klitte awards the away team a throw-in.
Orebro have a dangerous throw-in.
In the minute 26, In Orebro Norrkoping attack through Pontus Almqvist. The finish is off target, however.
Goal kick for Orebro at Behrn Arena.
Free kick for Orebro in their own half.
In the minute 29, Deniz Hummet scores to make it 1-0 at Behrn Arena.
That's a fine assist from Kevin Wright.
Can Norrkoping capitalize from this dangerous free kick?
In the minute 32, Fredrik Klitte awards Orebro a goal kick.
Free kick for Norrkoping in the half of Orebro.
Rasmus Lauritsen is on target to level the scores at 1-1.
In the minute 34, Throw-in for Norrkoping in the half of Orebro.
Christoffer Nyman puts the ball in the net and the away team now lead 1-2.
Great play from Sead Haksabanovic to set up the goal.
In the minute 37, Free kick Orebro.
Fredrik Klitte signals a free kick to Norrkoping in their own half.
Deniz Hummet grabs a goal to bring things level at 2-2 at Behrn Arena.
In the minute 39, Johan Martensson with an assist there.
Fredrik Klitte signals a free kick to Norrkoping in their own half.
Fredrik Klitte signals a free kick to Orebro.
In the minute 41, Christopher Telo (Norrkoping) gets a yellow card.
In Orebro a free kick has been awarded the home team.
Norrkoping have a goal kick.
In the minute 44, Norrkoping awarded a free kick in their own half.
Ball goes out of play for a Orebro goal kick.
At Behrn Arena the fourth official shows that 1 minutes will be added to the 1st half.
In the minute 45, Ball safe as Norrkoping is awarded a throw-in in their half.
It's a goal kick for the away team in Orebro.
The first-half is over.
In the minute 46, The second-half is underway at Behrn Arena.
Throw-in Orebro.
Throw-in high up the field for Norrkoping in Orebro.
In the minute 49, Throw-in for Orebro at Behrn Arena.
Free kick in a good position for Orebro!
Orebro have been awarded a corner by Fredrik Klitte.
In the minute 51, Free kick for Norrkoping in their own half.
Orebro apply pressure and a brilliant scoring opportunity is created for Nahir Besara. But the ball crashes against the crossbar!
Corner awarded to Orebro.
In the minute 54, Free kick Norrkoping.
Orebro have a goal kick.
Orebro have been awarded a penalty in Orebro...
In the minute 56, Isak Bergmann Johanneson (Norrkoping) has been given a yellow card and will be suspended from the next match.
Goal! The home team take a 3-2 lead thanks to a penalty from Nahir Besara.
Jens Gustafsson is making the team's first substitution at Behrn Arena with Jonathan Levi replacing Isak Bergmann Johanneson.
In the minute 59, Goal! Pontus Almqvist equalizes to bring the score to 3-3.
Filip Dagerstal instrumental with a fine assist.
Norrkoping are in shooting range from this free kick.
In the minute 61, Important block from the Orebro defence as Sead Haksabanovic fires in a strike for Norrkoping.
Norrkoping have been awarded a corner by Fredrik Klitte.
Fredrik Klitte awards Orebro a goal kick.
In the minute 63, Corner awarded to Norrkoping.
Fredrik Klitte signals a free kick to Orebro in their own half.

Fredrik Klitte signals a free kick to Norrkoping.
Fredrik Klitte signals a free kick to Norrkoping.

Sead Haksabanovic for Norrkoping gets in a strike but fails to hit the target.
Goal kick for Orebro at Behrn Arena.
In the minute 69, Orebro awarded a free kick in their own half.
Orebro drive upfield and David Seger gets in a shot. The strike is blocked by a Norrkoping defender.
Fredrik Klitte signals a Norrkoping throw-in in Orebro's half.
In the minute 70, Jens Gustafsson (Norrkoping) is making a second substitution, with Lars Gerson replacing Christopher Telo.
Alexander Fransson is replacing Eric Smith for the away team.
Can Orebro get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Norrkoping's half?
In the minute 73, Can Norrkoping capitalize from this throw-in deep inside Orebro's half?
Free kick for Norrkoping in their own half.
Play has been temporarily suspended for attention to Nahir Besara for Orebro who is writhing in pain on the pitch.
In the minute 76, Kevin Wright is writhing in pain and play has been suspended for a few moments.
Pontus Almqvist (Norrkoping) gets up for a header but cannot keep the ball on target.
Ball goes out of play for a Orebro goal kick.
Throw-in Orebro.
In the minute 78, Linus Hallenius is on a sub for Pontus Almqvist for Norrkoping.
Henrik Castegren is replacing Linus Wahlqvist for Norrkoping at Behrn Arena.
In the minute 78, Kevin Wright, who was grimacing earlier, has been substituted. Ali Hussein is the substitute for Orebro.
Orebro’s Nahir Besara is on his feet again at Behrn Arena.
Orebro will need to be alert as they defend a dangerous free kick from Norrkoping.
In the minute 81, Ball safe as Orebro is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Throw-in for Norrkoping close to the penalty box.
The home team replace David Seger with Martin Broberg.
In the minute 83, Free kick for Orebro in the half of Norrkoping.
Norrkoping pushes forward through Linus Hallenius, whose finish on goal is saved.
Fredrik Klitte awards the home team a throw-in.
In the minute 85, A throw-in for the home team on the opposite half.
Ali Hussein (Orebro) has received a yellow card from Fredrik Klitte.
Norrkoping awarded a free kick in their own half.
In the minute 87, Free kick Orebro.
Alexander Fransson for Norrkoping has been booked by Fredrik Klitte and receives a first yellow card.
In Orebro a free kick has been awarded the away team.
In the minute 88, Free kick for Orebro in their own half.
Throw-in for Norrkoping at Behrn Arena.
The home team have replaced Johan Martensson with Rasmus Karjalainen. This is the third substitution made today by Axel Kjall.
In the minute 89, Orebro make their fourth substitution with Daniel Bjorkman replacing Michael Almeback.
Throw-in high up the field for Norrkoping in Orebro.
Linus Hallenius of Norrkoping is pulled up for offside.
5 minutes will be added to the 2nd half in Orebro.
Norrkoping awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Free kick for Norrkoping in the half of Orebro.
Norrkoping have been awarded a corner by Fredrik Klitte.
It's a goal kick for the home team in Orebro.
Free kick Norrkoping.
Fredrik Klitte signals a free kick to Norrkoping.
Fredrik Klitte blows to end the match. The final score is 4-3.
Goal! Deniz Hummet gives Orebro a 4-3 lead in Orebro.
That's a fine assist from Rasmus Karjalainen.
Deniz Hummet (Orebro) has been booked and will miss the next match due to a suspension.
